    "media:imagetext": "Fastern Air Lines Picture\nThis Curtiss Condor Model I-32 was once the pride of Eastern Air Lines.\nHaving accommodations for 15 passengers, the biplane had a maximum pay-\nload of 2,455 pounds. Its two 750 horsepower Wright engines, had a top\nspeed of 165 miles per hour as compared with speeds of modern 10000008\nSilverliners in excess of 300 miles per hour. Retired in 1935 after two\nyears' service, the I-32 is still remembered as the \"last word\" in\nluxurious air travel, at the time of its inception.",
